{
  "text": "In [CITATION_1] it was shown that the summation over the CS uniform phases in the ray coefficients leads to channel elements which are very closely approximated by Gaussian variables. Hence, ray-based channels can often be interpreted as similar to correlated Gaussian channels where the Gaussianity arises via the summation over the random phases and the correlation structure is user-specific and driven by the ray powers and the angles of the rays. [CITATION_2] From (1) and the properties of the \u03b3 (l) c,s coefficients we average over the ray phases only to obtain the local correlation matrix, R l , for user l as",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "52962065",
